  "data": "{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"returncode\": 0,\n  \"stdout\": \"==========================================================================================\\nMERCHANT SOLAR REVENUE vs PPA REVENUE COMPARISON \\u2014 ERCOT WEST HUB (2021-2024)\\n==========================================================================================\\n\\nASSUMPTIONS:\\n  \\u2022 No curtailment \\u2014 all solar generation is sold at market\\n  \\u2022 Solar production profile = actual ERCOT system-wide solar generation profile\\n  \\u2022 Merchant revenue = solar-weighted average LMP at ERCOT West Hub\\n  \\u2022 PPA prices include RECs: $28, $40, $45, $46/MWh for 2021-2024\\n  \\u2022 REC-only price: $2.50/MWh\\n  \\u2022 PPA energy-only price = PPA price - REC value\\n\\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\nMetric                                              2021       2022       2023       2024\\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\nPPA Price (incl. RECs) [$/MWh]                    $28.00     $40.00     $45.00     $46.00\\nREC Value [$/MWh]                                  $2.50      $2.50      $2.50      $2.50\\nPPA Energy-Only Price [$/MWh]                     $25.50     $37.50     $42.50     $43.50\\nMerchant Revenue (RTM) [$/MWh]                    $78.37     $74.25     $72.67     $21.32\\nMerchant Revenue (DAM) [$/MWh]                    $92.03     $84.00     $99.91     $27.40\\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\nMerchant RTM - PPA (incl. RECs) [$/MWh]          +$50.37    +$34.25    +$27.67    -$24.68\\nMerchant RTM - PPA (energy-only) [$/MWh]         +$52.87    +$36.75    +$30.17    -$22.18\\nMerchant DAM - PPA (incl. RECs) [$/MWh]          +$64.03    +$44.00    +$54.91    -$18.60\\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\n\\nPERCENTAGE DIFFERENCES (Merchant vs PPA incl. RECs):\\n  2021: RTM merchant revenue was +179.9% vs PPA | DAM merchant revenue was +228.7% vs PPA\\n  2022: RTM merchant revenue was +85.6% vs PPA | DAM merchant revenue was +110.0% vs PPA\\n  2023: RTM merchant revenue was +61.5% vs PPA | DAM merchant revenue was +122.0% vs PPA\\n  2024: RTM merchant revenue was -53.7% vs PPA | DAM merchant revenue was -40.4% vs PPA\\n\\n==========================================================================================\\nKEY FINDINGS\\n==========================================================================================\\n\\n1. 2021-2023: Merchant revenues MASSIVELY outperformed PPA prices.\\n   \\u2022 RTM solar-weighted revenues were $-3/MWh ABOVE PPA prices in 2021,\\n     $-3/MWh above in 2022, and $-2/MWh above in 2023.\\n   \\u2022 This was driven by Winter Storm Uri (Feb 2021), summer scarcity pricing,\\n     and high gas prices in 2022-2023.\\n\\n2. 2024: The relationship REVERSED \\u2014 merchant revenues FELL BELOW PPA prices.\\n   \\u2022 RTM solar-weighted revenue collapsed to $21.32/MWh, ~$24.68/MWh BELOW the\\n     $46/MWh PPA price (and $22.18/MWh below the energy-only PPA of $43.50/MWh).\\n   \\u2022 This reflects the 'solar cannibalization' effect: as ERCOT solar capacity\\n     surged (solar MWh grew 3x from 2021 to 2024), midday prices collapsed.\\n\\n3. The solar-weighted price is MUCH lower than the simple average LMP in 2021\\n   ($78 vs $146) because solar produces during low-price midday hours, while\\n   high prices occurred during non-solar hours (e.g., early morning, evening).\\n\\n4. PPA holders had STABLE, PREDICTABLE revenue across all 4 years ($28-46/MWh),\\n   while merchant exposure ranged from $21 to $92/MWh \\u2014 extreme volatility.\\n\\n5. The REC-only value of $2.50/MWh is a small fraction of total PPA value\\n   (5-9%), meaning the energy component dominates the economics.\\n\",\n  \"stderr\": \"\"\n}",
